INSERT INTO `trh_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2014-05-16 17:20:37','2014-05-16 17:20:37','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','publish','open','open','','hello-world','','','2014-05-16 17:20:37','2014-05-16 17:20:37','',0,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(5,1,'2014-05-16 19:27:56','2014-05-16 19:27:56','<p>We believe that school is a place for teaching and learning, where students feel safe, secure and supported. To provide this supportive learning environment, school communities must foster respect among all members of the school community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our school code of conduct is based on the belief that there are values fundamental to the well being of both the individual and society and that we are all responsible for the choices we make. It encourages students to recognize, respect diversity and individual differences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the process, we want students to develop self-discipline, self-respect which can be considered as the core of any person\'s growth.  We expect our students to maintain high standards of personal conduct that includes honesty, discipline, integrity, respect,  personal & social ethics and values.</p>','About Us','','publish','open','open','','about-us','','','2014-05-17 11:50:25','2014-05-17 11:50:25','',0,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?page_id=5',0,'page','',0),(6,1,'2014-05-16 19:27:56','2014-05-16 19:27:56','About Us','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-v1','','','2014-05-16 19:27:56','2014-05-16 19:27:56','',5,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(7,1,'2014-05-17 11:33:49','2014-05-17 11:33:49','<p>We believe that school is a place for teaching and learning, where students feel safe, secure and supported. To provide this supportive learning environment, school communities must foster respect among all members of the school community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our school code of conduct is based on the belief that there are values fundamental to the well being of both the individual and society and that we are all responsible for the choices we make. It encourages students to recognize, respect diversity and individual differences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the process, we want students to develop self-discipline, self-respect which can be considered as the core of any person\'s growth.  We expect our students to maintain high standards of personal conduct that includes honesty, discipline, integrity, respect,  personal & social ethics and values.</p>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-v1','','','2014-05-17 11:33:49','2014-05-17 11:33:49','',5,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2014-05-18 05:46:32','2014-05-18 05:46:32','<blockquote>\"For Surely I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, plans for your welfare and not for harm , to give you a future with hope. Then when you call upon me and come and pray to me, I will hear you. When you search for me, you will find me, if you seek me with all your heart, I will let you find me, and I will restore your fortune.\"\r\n\r\n<small>Jer 29/11-14</small></blockquote>\r\nI begin by thanking God Almighty Father who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during this academic year.\r\n\r\nThe goal of our institute, \"Knowledge for Service, especially the marginalized and poor and especially the girls, through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His Kingdom\" resonates clearly through all the educational activities conducted all through the year. It is said, \"The mark of an educated mind is to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it\". It is our endeavor to instill in today’s children to be seekers of God Experience, wisdom and knowledge and preparing them to face the future with undaunted courage and excellence. All our activities in the school gear towards the same goal.\r\n\r\nThe current educational system promotes rote learning. The emphasis traditionally has been on vertical thinking which is effective but incomplete. The same has to be supplemented with the generative qualities of reflective thinking. It means solving problems through an indirect and creative approach. A child must learn to use reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involve ideas that may not be obtainable by using only traditional step-by-step logic. There is a need to ignite in the young mind to activate the right brain to develop their skills of creativity. The multiple intelligences dormant in our students must be tapped. So here is an effort to promote all these competencies through our various activities such as sports, literary works, talents day, club activity, fun fair, computer education, Smart class, school awards many other related activities which rejuvenate inner energy of the student to have potential and genuine personality growth. Educating the mind without educating the heart is no education at all.\" Aristotle\r\n\r\nI place on record the guidance of our management, the service of committed band of our staff- teaching and non-teaching, supportive parents, sportive students and benevolent benefactors. This has enabled us to march ahead with zeal and enthusiasm making progress mustering strength to run with both tiny and huge steps. St Therese of Child Jesus is our patroness guiding all our aspirations and commitments. May she inspire all of us to continue with the same rhythm and caliber?”Her encouraging thought is \" Be faithful over little things\".\r\n<h2 class=\"well alert alert-success\" align=\"center\">May God bless us all.</h2>','Principal Message','','publish','open','open','','principal-message','','','2014-05-18 10:43:22','2014-05-18 10:43:22','',5,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(9,1,'2014-05-18 05:46:32','2014-05-18 05:46:32','\"For Surely I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, plans for your welfare and not for harm ,