ality growth. Educating the mind without educating the heart is no education at all.\" Aristotle\r\n\r\nI place on record the guidance of our management, the service of committed band of our staff- teaching and non-teaching, supportive parents, sportive students and benevolent benefactors. This has enabled us to march ahead with zeal and enthusiasm making progress mustering strength to run with both tiny and huge steps. St Therese of Child Jesus is our patroness guiding all our aspirations and commitments. May she inspire all of us to continue with the same rhythm and caliber?”Her encouraging thought is \" Be faithful over little things\".\r\nMay God bless us all.','Principal Message','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 05:46:32','2014-05-18 05:46:32','',8,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','','Academics','','publish','open','open','','academics','','','2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','',0,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?page_id=10',0,'page','',0),(11,1,'2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','','Academics','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 06:05:17','2014-05-18 06:05:17','',10,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(12,1,'2014-05-18 06:07:47','2014-05-18 06:07:47','<ol>\r\n	<li>The school is open to all girls without any distinction of race, caste, creed and social status.</li>\r\n	<li>The school follows the syllabus prescribed by the Karnataka State Education Board. The medium of instruction is English and Kannada.</li>\r\n	<li>Students are admitted to standard VIII only.</li>\r\n	<li>Most of the students admitted are those who have successfully passed out from 7<sup>th</sup> Std of St.Teresa’s Higher Primary school.</li>\r\n	<li>Students who are coming from other schools have to clear an entrance test in Mathematics, Science, and English.</li>\r\n	<li>A pupil who has attended any unrecognized school cannot be admitted without a school leaving certificate (T.C) of the school previously attended, duely counter signed by the BEO of that range.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents seeking admission for their children should apply in writing in the prescribed application and pay the fees and agree to abide by the rules and regulations of the school.</li>\r\n	<li>Fees, once paid at the time of admission, are not refundable in any case.</li>\r\n	<li>The management has the last word in all matters relating to admission.</li>\r\n	<li>All the necessary documents such as Birth certificate, Caste certificate, Income certificate, Bank A/C etc, must be submitted in photo copies, self attested by the parents.</li>\r\n	<li>True and complete information is to be furnished in the application. In case of any discrepancy, the management holds the right to cancel the admission of the child.</li>\r\n</ol>','Admission','','publish','open','open','','admission','','','2014-05-18 06:07:47','2014-05-18 06:07:47','',10,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?page_id=12',0,'page','',0),(13,1,'2014-05-18 06:07:47','2014-05-18 06:07:47','<ol>\r\n	<li>The school is open to all girls without any distinction of race, caste, creed and social status.</li>\r\n	<li>The school follows the syllabus prescribed by the Karnataka State Education Board. The medium of instruction is English and Kannada.</li>\r\n	<li>Students are admitted to standard VIII only.</li>\r\n	<li>Most of the students admitted are those who have successfully passed out from 7<sup>th</sup> Std of St.Teresa’s Higher Primary school.</li>\r\n	<li>Students who are coming from other schools have to clear an entrance test in Mathematics, Science, and English.</li>\r\n	<li>A pupil who has attended any unrecognized school cannot be admitted without a school leaving certificate (T.C) of the school previously attended, duely counter signed by the BEO of that range.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents seeking admission for their children should apply 