li>We encourage the students to be enriched by their own cultural heritage to dedicate themselves to people of every race, culture, language and nationality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSpecial thrust of our educational effort is an active concern to make our students authentic and responsible citizens, to build a just and humane society.','Vision and Mission','','publish','open','open','','vision-and-mission','','','2014-05-18 06:30:21','2014-05-18 06:30:21','',5,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?page_id=14',0,'page','',0),(15,1,'2014-05-18 06:28:30','2014-05-18 06:28:30','<strong>School Motto:-</strong> Knowledge for Service\r\n<h3>Our Vision for Education As Salesian Missionaries of Mary Immaculate (SMMI)</h3>\r\nCalled to live in God’s presence and share in Christ’s mission to transform the world into Love. Like Mary we, the SMMI sisters respond to God’s call in the footsteps of Christ, the teacher par excellence, sharing the vision of our founders Fr. Henri Chaumont. We are called to be imbued with a daring zeal to give the less fortunate a sense of hope, so that there is a better tomorrow for them.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We strive to develop the potential of our students by fostering in them human, moral, social and spiritual values.</li>\r\n	<li>We enable them to foster our spiritual heritage and help them to respond to life’s challenges with hope, courage and perseverance and a deep faith in God.</li>\r\n	<li>We encourage them to be rooted in prayer and motivate them to commit themselves to serve the society and world at large.</li>\r\n	<li>We work for formation of right values for a better choice and decision making in our students.</li>\r\n	<li>We encourage the students to be enriched by their own cultural heritage to dedicate themselves to people of every race, culture, language and nationality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSpecial thrust of our educational effort is an active concern to make our students authentic and responsible citizens, to build a just and humane society.','Vision and Mission','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 06:28:30','2014-05-18 06:28:30','',14,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(16,1,'2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','','Students','','publish','open','open','','students','','','2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','',0,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?page_id=16',0,'page','',0),(17,1,'2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','','Students','','inherit','open','open','','16-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 09:16:41','2014-05-18 09:16:41','',16,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/16-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(18,1,'2014-05-18 09:20:48','2014-05-18 09:20:48','<h3>Achievements:</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n  We are pleased to  announce that our school is tagged with ISRD High Commission London.  Some of our students have successfully  cleared the district, state and National level Auditions. Varshitha of VIII &lsquo;D&rsquo;  has been selected as the &quot;Top talent student&rdquo; from our institution.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>We are Glad that our  school has got Accreditation and will be one of the Global Delivery Center in  Bangalore, Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Medals and Awards</h3>\r\n  <p>Our students have  appeared for various examination like Chinthana   and Taramandal science examination Navodaya  Kannada Examination and All India General Knowledge examination. Neetu, of X  &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the central merit scholarship in the All India General knowledge  exam.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Rachana J. Shetty</strong> of  VIII &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the second prize in state level singing competition conducted  by the Department of Education.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students have  secured the first prize in folk song conducted by the Lion&rsquo;s Club.  Keerthana and Vinaya Varshini of our girl- guides  are ever prepared to stretch their helping hands in social activities of our  school.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Kum.Raksha</strong> of X &lsquo;A&rsquo; Shwetha.  V Pravalika, Thaniya, Priyanka and Ayesha of X &lsquo;C&rsquo; are all set to receive  Rajyapuraskar award from the Governor of Karnataka.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students got the  first prize in the district level mock parliament competition conducted by the  Department of Education. Kum.Shambavi of IX &lsquo;B&rsquo; was selected for the state  level Mock Parliament Competition.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>The high school students were adjudged winners  in Throw ball, Volley ball and Shuttle Badminton competition at the Zonal level  sports.  They secured the first place in  Shot put and Discus Throw and the third place in Javelin throw at the Zonal  level.  At the Taluk level, they were  adjudged winners in Table tennis and Basket ball.  Our students participated in the district  level Table tennis Competition.</p>','Results and Achievements','','publish','open','open','','results-and-achievements','','','2014-05-18 09:22:58','2014-05-18 09:22:58','',16,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/?page_id=18',0,'page','',0),(19,1,'2014-05-18 09:20:48','2014-05-18 09:20:48','<h3>Achievements:</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n  We are pleased to  announce that our school is tagged with ISRD High Commission London.  Some of our students have successfully  cleared the district, state and National level Auditions. Varshitha of VIII &lsquo;D&rsquo;  has been selected as the &quot;Top talent student&rdquo; from our institution.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>We are Glad that our  school has got Accreditation and will be one of the Global Delivery Center in  Bangalore, Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Medals and Awards</h3>\r\n  <p>Our students have  appeared for various examination like Chinthana   and Taramandal science examination Navodaya  Kannada Examination and All India General Knowledge examination. Neetu, of X  &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the central merit scholarship in the All India General knowledge  exam.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Rachana J. Shetty</strong> of  VIII &lsquo;A&rsquo; has won the second prize in state level singing competition conducted  by the Department of Education.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students have  secured the first prize in folk song conducted by the Lion&rsquo;s Club.  Keerthana and Vinaya Varshini of our girl- guides  are ever prepared to stretch their helping hands in social activities of our  school.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><strong>Kum.Raksha</strong> of X &lsquo;A&rsquo; Shwetha.  V Pravalika, Thaniya, Priyanka and Ayesha of X &lsquo;C&rsquo; are all set to receive  Rajyapuraskar award from the Governor of Karnataka.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>Our students got the  first prize in the district level mock parliament competition conducted by the  Department of Education. Kum.Shambavi of IX &lsquo;B&rsquo; was selected for the state  level Mock Parliament Competition.</p>\r\n  \r\n<p>The high school students were adjudged winners  in Throw ball, Volley ball and Shuttle Badminton competition at the Zonal level  sports.  They secured the first place in  Shot put and Discus Throw and the third place in Javelin throw at the Zonal  level.  At the Taluk level, they were  adjudged winners in Table tennis and Basket ball.  Our students participated in the district  level Table tennis Competition.</p>','Results and Achievements','','inherit','open','open','','18-revision-v1','','','2014-05-18 09:20:48','2014-05-18 09:20:48','',18,'http://stdbksgirlshighschool.com/18-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2014-05-18 10:29:12','2014-05-18 10:29:12','<blockquote>\"For Surely I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, plans for your welfare and not for harm , to give you a future with hope. Then when you call upon me and come and pray to me, I will hear you. When you search for me, you will find me, if you seek me with all your heart, I will let you find me, and I will restore your fortune.\" \r\n<small>Jer 29/11-14</small>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nI begin by thanking God Almighty Father who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during