\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',24,0,3,'','',1,27,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',1,'*',''),(78,186,'About Us','about','','<div class=\"green\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<p class=\"bluefill\" style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The towering structure of Gulabi School that magnificently stands today at the cross-road of <strong>Jayamahal Extension</strong> is a symbol of pride and achievement of the school community of Gulabi. The present glory is a story of the past endeavors of those who contributed towards it. Gulabi remembers them with respect and gratitude.</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"> </span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div style=\"width: 50%; float: left;\">\r\n<div class=\"quote-cloud\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 19.1875px; text-align: center;\">The Founder Servant of God <strong>FC Mascarenhas</strong></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<br /> <img class=\"border_img3\" src=\"images/th 1.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"351\" height=\"263\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"width: 50%; float: left;\">\r\n<p> <strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #0099ff;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Mgr RFC Mascarenhas</strong></span></span></strong><strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #0099ff;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">, </span></span></strong><strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong> </strong></span></strong><strong style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Callibri; color: #2a2a2a; line-height: 0.49cm;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">the ‘Servant of God’ and the founder of the Bethany Congregation foresaw that the presence of Bethany Sisters in the capital city of Karnataka State would facilitate transactions in the Education Department and with the Government Officials. He with Sr Precilla, the then Superior General visited his friend Archbishop Thomas Pothacamury in 1995, seeking a suitable site in the Archdiocese of Bangalore. Mean while they obtained the necessary permission from Rt Rev Raymond D’Mello, the Bishop of angalore to erect a religious house in Bangalore Archdiocese. Ten months before the Founder’s death, a house at Jayamahal Extension was rented by Sr MAcrina, the superior General that became the first Bethany house in Bangalore. It was blessed by Arcbhishop Thomas Pothacamury on 19.03.1960.</span></span></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt;\">The pioneers:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>                     <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">On 18march 1960, the pioneers Sr Anysia, Sr Julitta accomplished by Mother Macrina arrived in Bangalore. Mr Gregory Mathias, the Finance Secretary to the Government of Karnataka and his wife Ms Y Mathias – the uncle and aunt of Sr Laeta and late Sr Getta were instrumental in finding a rented house and procuring a site for the school and the convent. The rented house was named ‘Villa Theresa’ after the popular name “Little Flower” – St Therease of the Child Jesus, the second patroness of Bethany Congregation and the School – “Gulabi” under the patronage of the same saint.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The Initial Innings:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>      <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">On 18march 1960, the pioneers Sr Anysia, Sr Julitta accomplished by Mother Macrina arrived in Bangalore. Mr Gregory Mathias, the Finance Secretary to the Government of Karnataka and his wife Ms Y Mathias – the uncle and aunt of Sr Laeta and late Sr Getta were instrumental in finding a rented house and procuring a site for the school and the convent. The rented house was named ‘Villa Theresa’ after the popular name “Little Flower” – St Therease of the Child Jesus, the second patroness of Bethany Congregation and the School – “Gulabi” under the patronage of the same saint. The Initial Innings: The Archbishop of Bangalore laid the foundation stone for the school on 15 April 1961. Twenty-one tiny tots seeking good educations were enrolled into the portals of Gulabi School on 22 May,1960. The first block of the building was blessed on 23.05.1962. The school was accorded Education Departmental Recognition in 1962. Classes were added year that reached standard VII in the year 1966. By 1963 over 400 students were enrolled and Sr Anysia, the first headmistress of Gulabi School organized its first Annual Day on 24 January 1963 in collaboration with her staff. On 31 January,1965the sisters vacated the renter house and occupied the part of the school building for their residence and continued to concentrate on education.            </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong><strong><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">From Trickle to a Torrent:</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>   <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">In 1967, Sr Fides upgraded the Primary School into High School with standard VIII, and the classes were housed in the premises of the Archdiocesan Social Wing - ‘Workers’ center”. IN 1973 they were shifted back to the newly constructed second floor of the present school building, Sr. Agnella’s arrival on June 9th 1973 as the Headmistress of the fully established High School, gave a new thrust and the school started marching towards great heights. Through her vision, passion and dedication she left indelible mark in the hearts of students and teachers and carved a niche in Bethany. This great Stalwart and eminent educationalist will continue to shine in the annals of Gulabi.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> <span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Sr Agnella was very concerned about suitable residence for sisgers away from school premises. Sr Elizabeth who took over as the superior of the convent and paid attention to this and shouldered the task of putting up a convent, in spite of financial stress. A site was purchased on the Nandidurga road and on 3rd December 1997 the present Convent building was inaugurated with the name ‘Bethany Convent’. Presently, Sr Flossy the animator keeps the community lively with the co-operation of the sisters, young and old. The presence of sr Lucina, the senior most member is a blessing and boon to the community with her young and energetic spirit. Sr Ann Teresa, who was the secretary of BES at one time and who was also elected as the President of AINACS, involves herself actively in the field of education as a resource person at various levels.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Following the foot steps of the great teacher –Jesus and being convinced of the importance of His teachings, Gulabi School strives to instill in the students, the BES Vision and Core Values through various activites. Gulabi studet guided by their teachers keep themselves abreast of times by involving actively in different movements like Y.S.M, Science – Eco – Mathematics clubs, Sevadal and Bosco Kids and channelize their energy creatively. The Girl-guide unit has brought Laurels to the School at state and national levels. The socio-religious and national days are celebrated with due respect and festivity.</span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; background: #ffffff; line-height: 0.49cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #0099ff;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\">A seed is sown :</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; border: none; padding: 0cm;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">On</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> the 22nd of May in the year 1960, 21 tiny tots carrying little bags with lots of </span></span></span></span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">hopes and dreams entered the portals of Gulabi School, that was the curtain raiser. The School was named after Saint Therese of Lisieux also called Little Flower. She lived in France, in the 14th Century.<img src=\"images/videos/seed.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" style=\"float: right;\" /></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.13cm; margin-bottom: 0.13cm; border: none; padding: 0cm; font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.5cm;\"><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">A Cloistered Nun who attained the height of sanctity, by way of spiritual childhood a way of trust and surrender to God. She related to God as a loving Father. A short life ..... a premature death at 24, but a fruitful endeavour to love and serve selflessly. Before breathing her last, she is believed to have said,</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.13cm; margin-bottom: 0.13cm; border: none; padding: 0cm; font-variant: normal; line-height: 0.5cm;\"><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\">“<span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">My Mission – To make God loved begins after my death. I will spend my Heaven doing good on Earth.I will let fall a shower of Roses “. Her love for Jesus and a deeper passion for human kind is manifested in the School motto which reads ‘</span></span><span style=\"color: #0066cc;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><strong>BLOOM FORTH IN LOVE FOR LOVE’.</strong></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.18cm; margin-bottom: 0.18cm; line-height: 0.49cm; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><strong><span style=\"color: #2a2a2a;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">A tiny seed of faith and hope planted in 1960 on very thin soil with 21 students on roll watered with relentless perseverance, determination and the fear of God has grown from strength to strength to the strength of 1798 students. These are undoubtedly the marvels, miracles and mercies of the Lord.</span></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> </span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<hr title=\"Our Goal\" alt=\"goal\" class=\"system-pagebreak\" />\r\n<p class=\"core\" style=\"font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; line-height: 21px; color: #000066; margin: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-left: 15px; padding-right: 15px; width: 590px; font-weight: bold;\">To promote the glory of God by the holiness of the members of our institute and the service of the Kingdom of God</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br style=\"color: #4c4c4c; font-family: verdana; font-size: medium; font-weight: bold;\" /><strong class=\"style5\" style=\"color: #ff6400; font-family: verdana; font-size: medium;\">   Our Goal</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<div class=\"core\" style=\"font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; line-height: 21px; color: #000066; margin: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-left: 15px; padding-right: 15px; width: 590px; font-weight: bold;\">Education for fullness of life for all, especially the marginalized and <br />rural poor and the girls through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His kingdom</div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #4c4c4c; font-family: verdana; font-size: medium; font-weight: bold;\">   School Motto:    <span class=\"style5\" style=\"color: #ff6400;\">BLOOM FORTH IN LOVE FOR LOVE</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> </span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<hr title=\"Our Core Values\" alt=\"values\" class=\"system-pagebreak\" />\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\">- Good experience</span><br style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\">- Compassionate love for all, specially the poor and the marginalized </span><br style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\">- Communion, collaboration, team spirit.</span><br style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\">- Excellence in terms of developing each one\'s unique potentialities to build a    just and humane community.</span><br style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\">- Truth, love, Justice and peace.</span><br style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\">- Simplicity of life style and dignity of labour.</span><br style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000066; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 21px;\">- Respect for life, nature, cultures, Religion and love for the Nation.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>','',-2,0,0,81,'2013-12-31 04:08:02',246,'','2014-01-17 15:05:29',249,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-12-31 04:08:02','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',112,0,4,'','',1,304,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(82,194,'Achievements','achievements','','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> <strong style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Verdana, serif; color: #365f91; line-height: 150%;\">Nikitha Dazzlin Pinto</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">A winner in the lawn tennis at the state level conducted by the department of education and played at the national level in Pune.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"border_img3\" src=\"images/rajanna1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"191\" height=\"268\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 15px;\" /><span style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\">Bangalore being the hub of many scientific institutions, have</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">responded to this challenge and have shone at State and National level in</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">activities conducted by the Education Department, Nehru Planetarium and C V</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Raman Resarch Institute. They have come out in flying colours in the</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">following science exhibitions and science drama- ‘uses of water’, ‘Geothermal</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Energy’, ‘Recycling of Sewage water’, ‘Nuclear Energy’, ‘Energy from the</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">deep sea frozen ice’, and ‘who cares for life’. ‘The final judgment’ (2008) was</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">telecast on Doordarshan. A few individuals have climbed the ladder of fame</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">and they glitter in the galaxy of stars. Meenakhsi has joined ISRO as a scientist,</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Sushma Lobo participated in the ’Youth exchange programme’ in</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Hong Kong(1990). Similar activities have helped the students to gain more</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">confidence and are doing very well in the society, Sudha Narashivnraju is a</span></span></p>\r\n<p><br class=\"Apple-interchange-newline\" /><img src=\"images/vathsala.JPG\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"278\" height=\"185\" style=\"font-family: Callibri; font-size: 13px; float: right; cursor: se-resize !important;\" /><span style=\"font-family: Callibri; font-size: 10pt;\">Kannada film actress; Savitha N, Shilpa K and Shilpa Rudraappa are kannada serial</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">actress, while Pallavi R is a Radio jockey. Srishma H S won the state level science<br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">seminar and won the second prize in the national level and she had the privilege of</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">visiting the museum in Holland (2011). Nikitha D Pinto, a budding athlete of our</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">school has been playing lawn tennis several times in the national level.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">The new Gulabi auditorium is indeed a dream come true shared with expectations</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">and excitement by the students, staff, sisters, parents and well wishers</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Callibri;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">of Gulabi. The whole process of the auditorium a reality was a powerful experience</span></span></p>\r\n<p> </p>','',-2,0,0,14,'2014-01-15 16:43:24',246,'','2014-01-17 06:08:58',249,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2014-01-15 16:43:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',22,0,0,'','',1,72,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(79,187,'Principal\'s message','principal-s-message','','<div style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div style=\"width: 50%; float: left;\">\r\n<div style=\"float: left;\"><img class=\"border_img3\" src=\"images/principal.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"344\" height=\"222\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div style=\"color: blue; font-weight: bold; width: 50%; float: left; font-size: 16px;\"> </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: blue; font-weight: bold; width: 50%; float: left; font-size: 16px;\"> </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: blue; font-weight: bold; width: 50%; float: left; font-size: 16px;\"> </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: blue; font-weight: bold; width: 50%; float: left; font-size: 16px;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Happy are those who find wisdom and those who get understanding; For wisdom’s income is better than silver and her revenue is better than gold. (Wis. 3:13-14)</span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<div style=\"font-size: 13px;\">\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">I begin by thanking God almighty who is the author of all Wisdom and whose understanding has guided our steps during this academic year. </span></span></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The goal of our institute, “Education for fullness of life for all, especially the marginalized and rural poor and the girls, through an integrated formation, in partnership with God to build His Kingdom” resonates clearly through all the educational activities conducted all through the year. It is said, “The mark of aneducated mind is to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it”. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">It is our endeavour to instill intoday’s children to be seekers of God Experience, wisdom and knowledge and preparing them to face the future with undaunted courage and excellence. All our activities in the school gear towards the same goal.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\"><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">The current educational system promotes rote learning. The emphasis traditionally has been on vertical thinking which is effective but incomplete. The same has to be supplemented with the generative qualities of lateral thinking. It means solving problems through an indirect and creative approach. A child must learn to use reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involve ideas that may not be obtainable by using only traditional step-by-step logic. There is a need to ignite in the young to activate the right brain to develop their skills of creativity. The multiple intelligences dormant in our students must be tapped. So here is an effort to promote all these competencies through our magazine Gulabi Showers. It includes </span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">articles relating to science and technology, women, environment, puzzles, art and poems by our students.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant: normal; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;\" align=\"JUSTIFY\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\">I place on record the guidance of our management, the service of committed band of our staff- teaching and non-teaching, supportive parents, sportive students and benevolent benefactors. This has enabled us to march ahead with zeal and enthusiasm making progress mustering strength to run with both tiny and huge steps. St Therese of Child Jesus is our patroness guiding all our aspirations and commitments. May she inspire all of us to continue with the same rhythm and calibre.</span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"font-variant: normal; text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal;\">May God bless us all.</span></span></span></strong></h1>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','',-2,0,0,81,'2013-12-31 04:48:49',246,'','2014-01-17 05:00:49',249,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-12-31 04:48:49','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',39,0,1,'','',1,149,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(80,188,'Infrastructure','infrastructure','','<p class=\"greenfill\" style=\"color: blue;\">SCHOOL INFRASTRUCTURE</p>\r\n<p>The school consists of 2 floors. There are 40 classrooms in the school. The class rooms are spacious and have proper ventilation for conducive environment for learning.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><span class=\"style5\">LABORATORIES :</span></strong> The school is well equipped with laboratories. Students can conduct their practical lessons with ease, under the guidance of a teacher with ample scope for individual learning and an auditorium, which can comfortably accommodate more than a thousand students.</p>\r\n<p>The school has an excellent<strong> library</strong> which is spacious enough. The library has an exhaustive collection of books.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Karate classe</strong>s are held for the children from Classes 3rd to 7th, with a well trained instructor.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span class=\"style5\">Music and Dance:</span> Opportunity to learn music and dance is available for use by interested students. They provide an outlet for students to relax and let out tension.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"style5\">Playground :</span> with a vast playground and well experienced physical education instructor children are given all the benefit of having a healthy mind in a healthy body.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"border_img3\" src=\"http://gulabischool.org/images/comp.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Computer Lab\" width=\"331\" height=\"247\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 15px;\" />Gulabi school matches the <strong>best infrastructure and facilities</strong> required for imparting quality education to the wards of the parents from Indian Community. The school has got a science lab equipped with latest apparatus. The school has set up a well furnished<strong> library, a huge auditorium, a LCD Projector</strong> and other facilities like installation of Aqua Guard for safe drinking water, etc., Subjects like Mathematics, Social Science, languages and General Science are made interesting and meaningful through the use of technology in class rooms. The Computer lab of the school is capable of providing latest technological support and one on one learning of computers and related technological skills. The school has got a modern two storied building. The Class Rooms are well lit, spacious and airy, providing a conducing environment for learning.</p>','',-2,0,0,81,'2013-12-31 04:51:32',246,'','2014-01-16 05:52:49',246,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2013-12-31 04:51:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',7,0,2,'','',1,64,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(81,193,'Founder','founder','','<p class=\"bluefill\" style=\"color: black; font-size: 25px; text-align: center; font-weight: bold;\">The Founder of the Congregation</p>\r\n<div class=\"quote-cloud\" style=\"width: 300px; margin-left: 130px;\">\r\n<p class=\"jm-typo-title\" style=\"font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;\"><strong>Servant of God</strong>  <strong><span style=\"color: blue;\">Raymond Francis Camillus Mascarenhas</span></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 120px;\">           <img src=\"images/th 1.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"319\" height=\"239\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 40px;\" /></p>\r\n<div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: black;\">\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Raymond was born on 23 January 1875 to</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">J</span></span></span></strong><strong><span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">oanna and Lazarus Mascarenhas</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">of Mangalore, then residing at Shimoga.</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Having completed his academic and priestly</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">training in Mangalore, he was</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">ordained priest on 4 March 1900.</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">He rendered pastoral service at Kallianpur, </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Udyavar and Agrar.  At St Sebastian’s Bendur </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 180px;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Monsignor was the founder parish priest from 1914 to 1931.</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 180px;\"><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">A man with deep God experience, far sighted vision and deep intellectual insight and obsessed with the</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">idea of sharing God’s love especially with the poor, he read the signs of the times and founded the Congregation</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">of the Sisters of the Little Flower of Bethany in the year 1921 at Bendur to provide an opportunity to those who</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">desirous of answering the call of God to religious life and to cater to the pastoral care of the people and educational</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">needs of rural children, especially girls.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">He was a man of God, known to be a compassionate pastor, an eloquent speaker and powerful preacher,</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">an efficient administrator, an eminent educationist and a writer. Having served as the Vicar General of</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">the Diocese of Mangalore from 1931 to 1941 he continued to direct the Congregation that he founded.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">He dared to tread the unbeaten paths, where others dared not, while taking up new initiatives. In recognition</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.35cm; padding-left: 90px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">of his valuable services the Holy Father, Pope Pius the XII conferred on him the title – Domestic Prelate.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 90px;\"> </p>\r\n</div>','',-2,0,0,14,'2014-01-13 19:02:04',246,'','2014-01-23 06:03:15',252,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2014-01-13 19:02:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',42,0,1,'','',1,73,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'*',''),(84,203,'Attendacen Report for Last 15 da